PRIVACY POLICY
PLC Animator
Welcome to the Privacy Policy of PLC Academy (“licensor," "we," "us," or "our"). This Privacy Policy is designed to inform users ("licensee," "you," or "your") about the types of information we collect, how we use and share this information, the security measures we implement, your choices regarding your data, and how to contact us with privacy-related concerns. By accessing or using the PLC Animator application ("the App") and platform in general, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.
1.0
INTERNATIONAL USERS
The platform is hosted and administered in the Mexico and is governed by Mexican legislation.  Any personal information you submit will be sent to us in Mexico and will be stored on servers located in the Mexico.  You agree to have your personal information sent to the Mexico in order to get services on the PLC Animator: PLC Simulator.
If you are visiting a website from outside the Mexico, please be aware that Mexican law may not provide the same level of privacy protection as the law in your region.
2.0
INFORMATION COLLECTED
You agree that when you download, install, use, access, or otherwise engage with the application or website, we may use automated techniques to gather information about your Device and about you and your use of the application and the Services.
You may also be needed to supply some information about yourself in order to download, install, or use the application or certain of its features or capabilities, and the application may allow other users to share relevant data about yourself and about others.
Our Privacy Policy applies to all information we collect via or in connection with our Applications and Websites. By downloading, installing, using, or giving information to or through our Applications and/or Websites, you indicate that you have received, read, and understood the terms of our Privacy Policy, and that you accept and consent to all actions done by us in accordance with the Privacy Policy.
Licensor’s use of your personal information shall be governed by this Privacy Policy. By using the Licensed Application, you indicate your understanding and acceptance of the Privacy Policy.
2.1
Types of Information
We collect personal and other information from you when you provide information to us or whenever you interact with us via the app and/or services. The following below are some of the ways Licensor collect information when you use the PLC Animator App:
Personal Information
:
When you interact with the App, we may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide. This includes your name, email address, contact details, and any other information you choose to share.
Information Provided through Communication
:  The app provides links or forms that can be used to contact us so you can comment, make a complaint, make suggestions and ask questions. Your name, email address, address, and phone number are requested on these forms so we can address our answer in a mannerly way. Licensor may store information from email on file, but does not currently sell or license this information with third parties without express authorization from you.
Device Information
:
We automatically collect certain information about your device and its usage of the App. This may include the device type, operating system, unique device identifiers, and mobile network information.
Usage Data
:
Through your use of the App, we gather data about how you interact with its features and content. This includes metrics such as app usage, features accessed, session duration, and performance data.
Information from Partners
: Licensor obtains information about account owners and their users from third-party companies, such as market data enrichment services, including information about an account owner’s company size or industry, contact information, or activity of certain enterprise domains. Licensor may also obtain information from third-party advertising partners who deliver ads displayed on PLC Animator Services, such as whether you clicked on an ad they showed you.
2.2
Methods of Collection
User-Provided Information:
You may provide personal information when creating an account, setting up your profile, or contacting customer support.
Automatically Collected Data:
We use cookies, log files, and other tracking technologies to collect information about your device and usage patterns. These technologies help us improve the functionality and performance of the App.
Third-Party Integrations:
Certain features of the App may require integration with third-party services, such as social media platforms. In such cases, your interactions with these services are governed by their respective privacy policies.
3.0
USE OF INFORMATION
3.1
How We Use Collected Information
We may use the information we collect from you when you register, make a subscription, sign up for our newsletter, respond to a survey or marketing communication, use the app services, or use certain other app features in the following ways:
Personalization and Customization
:
We use the information you provide to personalize your experience within the App. This includes customizing content, recommendations, and user interface elements based on your preferences.
App Improvement and Optimization
:
Your usage data helps us understand how users interact with the App. We analyze this data to identify areas for improvement, optimize performance, and enhance user experience.
Communication and Support
:
We may use your contact information to communicate with you regarding updates, announcements, or important notifications related to the App. This includes responding to inquiries and providing customer support.
Analytics and Research
:
Collected data is utilized for analytics purposes, such as tracking app usage trends, user demographics, and feature popularity. This helps us make informed decisions about future developments and enhancements.
When personal information is collected, we will inform you at the point of collection, including the purpose of the collection.  Licensor does not intend to transfer your personal information to third parties without your consent, except under the limited conditions described in the discussion entitled "Information Sharing or Disclosure" below. If you choose to provide us with your personal information, we may transfer that information to or to our third-party service providers.
3.2
Purposes of Information Usage
Enhancing User Experience
: By analyzing user behavior and preferences, we aim to create a more intuitive and user-friendly App interface. This includes refining navigation, optimizing feature placement, and improving overall usability.
Feature Development
: Insights gained from usage data inform the development of new features and functionalities. We strive to introduce innovative tools that align with user needs and preferences.
Bug Fixing and Troubleshooting
: Monitoring app performance metrics allows us to promptly identify and address technical issues. We conduct regular diagnostics to ensure a smooth and error-free user experience.
Content Recommendations
: Based on your usage patterns and interactions, we may recommend relevant content, tutorials, or resources within the App. This personalized approach aims to assist users in achieving their automation goals.
Through the detailed explanation of how we utilize the collected information, users gain a clear understanding of the purposes behind data processing within the App. Next, we discuss the circumstances under which user information may be shared.
4.0
SHARING OF INFORMATION
Except as described in this Privacy Policy, any information you provide to us will not be shared with or used by third parties without your permission.
4.1
Circumstances of Sharing
Service Providers
: We may engage trusted third-party service providers to assist in the operation and maintenance of the App. These service providers have access to your information solely to perform tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.
Other PLC Animator Mobile App Users
: Certain of your personal data may also be shared with other users of the PLC Animator App as part of the normal operation of the PLC Animator App. For example, your profile picture and biographical information that you add is accessible to all users.
Legal Compliance
: In cases where required by law or legal processes, we may disclose your information to comply with legal obligations. This includes responding to subpoenas, court orders, or other legal requests for information.
Business Transfers
: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, user information may be transferred as part of the transaction. We will ensure that any such transfer complies with privacy laws and regulations.
4.2
Third Parties
Analytics and Performance Monitoring
: We utilize analytics platforms to gather insights into App usage and performance. These third-party services help us improve our services by analyzing aggregated data trends.
Cloud Storage Providers
: Certain user data, such as account information and preferences, may be stored on cloud servers provided by reputable service providers. This enables seamless access to your information across devices and ensures data redundancy.
Marketing and Advertising Partners
: We may engage marketing and advertising partners to promote the App and reach a wider audience. These partners may collect anonymized data for targeted advertising purposes.
App Integrations
: When you choose to integrate the App with third-party services, such as social media platforms or cloud storage, your interactions with these services may result in data sharing.
Through these explanations, users gain insight into the reasons behind potential data sharing and the parties involved. Next, we discuss the measures taken to protect user information.
5.0
LEGAL BASIS FOR DATA PROCESSING
The legal basis we utilize is determined by the objective of the processing of personal data, which may be one of the following:
Contract
- pursuant to Article 6 (1) GDPR, in circumstances where we are required to process certain data in order to execute a contract, such as when a user agrees the EULA to use the program;
Consent
– in cases where a user chooses to send us data relating to the Privacy Statement, Marketing Statement, Antispam Statement, Supplemental Statement, Statement regarding Data Processing for PLC Academy Managed Protection, Statement regarding Data Processing for Web Control (previously known as Statement regarding Data Processing for Parental Control), Statement regarding Data Processing for Call Filter, Protection of Community, etc.
Legal duty
- pursuant to Article 6 (1) GDPR, in circumstances where we are required to handle data to satisfy legal requirements, such as for tax purposes;
Legitimate interest
- pursuant to point (f) of Article 6 (1) GDPR, in circumstances where we have legitimate interests as a cybersecurity firm unless such interests are exceeded by the user's interests or basic rights and freedoms. In such circumstances, for example, when personal data is kept in our infrastructure and assessed for recent and possible cyber threats using artificial intelligence and/or depending on our professionals' experience. Recital 49 of the GDPR recognizes that it is a company's legitimate interest to treat personal data to the extent required and appropriate to guarantee network and information security.
You may be able to exercise certain rights in relation to your personal data under some local legislation, such as those outlined in the section Your Rights and Options. Please contact us if you desire to exercise any of the rights outlined here hello@sticky-games.com.
6.0
DATA SECURITY
Protecting your privacy and securing your information is a top priority for us. In this section, we detail the measures and practices we employ to safeguard user data.
6.1
Measures Taken
Encryption Protocols
: We utilize industry-standard encryption protocols to secure data transmission and storage. This ensures that your information remains confidential and protected against unauthorized access.
Access Controls
: Access to user data is restricted to authorized personnel who require such information for legitimate business purposes. This helps prevent unauthorized viewing or handling of sensitive data.
Regular Security Audits
: We conduct periodic security audits and assessments to identify and address potential vulnerabilities. This proactive approach ensures that our security measures remain up-to-date and effective.
Data Minimization
: We only collect and retain the information necessary for the operation and improvement of the App. Unnecessary data is promptly deleted or anonymized to minimize risk.
User Authentication
: Certain features of the App may require user authentication or login credentials. We encourage users to create strong, unique passwords and enable additional security measures such as two-factor authentication.
While we implement robust security measures, it is important to note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. However, we continuously strive to maintain the highest standards of data protection.
7.0
DATA RETENTION
Because many users tend to use our service at different points, we retain your personal information for continued service and convenience purposes until you advise us not to do so.
We retain your personal data for as long as reasonably necessary to provide the services and fulfill the transactions you have requested, comply with our legal obligations, or for other legitimate business purposes, such as maintaining business and financial records, resolving disputes, maintaining security, detecting and preventing fraud and abuse, and enforcing our agreements. After the applicable retention period has elapsed, your personal data will be anonymized and deleted.
8.0
BREACH
If any information under our control is compromised as a consequence of a breach in our system security or the unintended dissemination of information, we shall make reasonable efforts to investigate the issue and provide notification of the network intrusion in compliance with relevant laws and guidelines.
9.0
USER CHOICES
We respect your privacy preferences and provide options for you to control how your information is used. In this section, we outline the choices available to users regarding their data.
9.1
Options Available
Privacy Settings
: Within the App settings, you have the ability to manage your privacy preferences. This includes opting in or out of certain data collection activities.
Cookie Preferences
: You can control the use of cookies and similar tracking technologies through your browser or device settings. Adjusting these preferences allows you to limit data collection for analytics or advertising purposes.
Communication Preferences
: You may choose to opt-in or opt-out of receiving promotional communications from us. This includes newsletters, updates, and marketing materials.
Account Deletion
: If you wish to delete your account and associated data from the App, you can do so through the account settings. Please note that this action is irreversible and will result in the loss of all account-related information.
Data Portability
: Upon request, we can provide you with a copy of your personal data in a commonly used electronic format. This allows you to transfer your information to another platform or service.
10.0
ACCESS AND UPDATE
Ensuring the accuracy and relevance of your personal information is important. In this section, we explain how you can access and update your data within the App.
10.1
How to Access and Update Information
Account Settings
: You can access and review your personal information by logging into your account within the App. Here, you can update your profile details, preferences, and communication settings.
Data Correction
: If you believe that any of the information we hold about you is inaccurate or incomplete, you can request corrections through the App settings or by contacting our support team.
Data Deletion
: Should you wish to delete specific data points or your entire account, you have the option to do so within the App. Deleted data is removed from our systems in accordance with our data retention policies.
Data Export
: Upon request, we can provide you with a copy of your data for personal reference or transfer. This includes account information, usage data, and any other information collected.
