CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
Protecting the privacy of children is of utmost importance to us. In this section, we address our compliance with children's privacy laws and restrictions on app usage by minors.
11.1
Compliance with Laws
Age Restrictions
: The App is intended for use by individuals who are [13/16/18] years of age or older, depending on the jurisdiction. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the applicable age limit without parental consent.
Parental Consent
: If we become aware that personal information has been collected from a child without parental consent, we will take steps to promptly delete such information from our systems.
Educational Use
: While the App may be valuable for educational purposes, it is important for parents and guardians to supervise minors' use of the App. We recommend parental guidance and oversight for minors using the App.
12.0
ACCOUNT CLOSURE / ERASURE
If you choose to terminate your PLC Animator account, your personal, non-public data will usually be removed from public view on our Services within 30 business days.
Exceptional cases:
We will maintain your personal information even after you delete your membership account if it is fairly in compliance with our legal responsibilities (including law enforcement requests), comply with regulations, settle disputes, ensure security, hinder fraud and illegal activities, or accomplish your request.
You acknowledge that information shared with others via the platform messaging, updates, or group posts will remain accessible after you delete your account or remove content from your own profile or inbox, and we have no control over the information that other users have replicated out of our platform.
The ratings or review information connected with closed accounts will be an unknown individual.
13.0
TERMINATION / SUSPENSION OF ACCOUNT
You agree that we may for legitimate reasons, in our sole discretion, and without your prior consent your consent, terminate your account.
Grounds for such termination may include:
extended periods of inactivity,
violation of this User Agreement,
fraudulent, harassing, or abusive behavior,
suspected illegal activities or investigated reports,
behavior that is harmful to other users, third parties, and the community ethos of our Application or our business interests.
In the event that we terminate your account, you may not register for the Application again without our express permission.
If you believe that any action has been taken against your account in error, please contact us at hello@sticky-games.com.
In addition, if we believe, in our sole discretion, that a violation of this User Agreement or suspected illegal activities or investigated reports has occurred, we may take any other corrective action we deem appropriate.
We reserve the right to investigate suspected violations of this User Agreement or illegal and inappropriate behavior by your or other users' reports via the Application because the Licensor has zero knowledge about encrypted chat messages.
Licensor will cooperate with local law enforcement investigation or court order requesting or directing us to disclose the identity, behavior, or activities of anyone believed to have violated this User Agreement or to have engaged in illegal behavior. Licensee may request termination of your account at any time and for any reason.
Any suspension or termination of your account shall not affect your obligations to Licensor under this User Agreement (including but not limited to ownership, indemnification, any representations and warranties made by you, and limitation of liability), which by their sense and context are intended to survive such suspension or termination.
14.0
FAIR INFORMATION PRACTICES
The Fair Information Practices Principles form the backbone of privacy law in the United States and the concepts they include have played a significant role in the development of data protection laws around the globe. Understanding the Fair Information Practice Principles and how they should be implemented is critical to comply with the various privacy laws that protect personal information.
In order to be in line with Fair Information Practices we will take the following responsive action, should a data breach occur, we will notify you via email and in-app notification within 7 business days.
We also agree to the Individual Redress Principle which requires that individuals have the right to legally pursue enforceable rights against data collectors and processors who fail to adhere to the law. This principle requires not only that individual have enforceable rights against data users, but also that individuals have here. We also agree to the Individual Redress Principle which requires that individuals have the right to legally pursue enforceable rights against data collectors and processors who fail to adhere to the law. This principle requires not only that individual have enforceable rights against data users, but also that individuals have recourse to courts or government agencies to investigate and/or prosecute non-compliance by data processors.
We believe in being accountable for the personal information we collect and process. We have designated a Privacy Officer who is responsible for overseeing our privacy practices, and we regularly review and update our policies and procedures to ensure that they are in line with current best practices and legal requirements.
In addition to these general principles, we also adhere to specific regulations and laws that govern the handling of personal information. For example, for users who are California residents, we comply with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), which provides additional rights and protections for residents of that state. We also comply with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) for users who are residents of the European Union, and the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA) for users who are residents of Canada.
Overall, our commitment to fair information practices is a fundamental aspect of how we operate the PLC Animator Platform. We understand that users trust us with their personal information, and we take that trust very seriously. By following these principles, we aim to build and maintain that trust, and ensure that users feel confident using our services.
15.0
CAN SPAM ACT
The CAN-SPAM Act is a law that sets the rules for commercial email, establishes requirements for commercial messages, gives recipients the right to have emails stopped from being sent to them, and spells out tough penalties for violations.
We collect your email address in order to send information, respond to inquiries, and/or other requests or questions.
To be in accordance with CANSPAM we agree to the following:
NOT use false or misleading subjects or email addresses.
Identify the message as an advertisement in some reasonable way.
Include the physical address of our business or site headquarters.
Monitor third-party email marketing services for compliance, if one is used.
Honour opt-out/unsubscribe requests quickly.
Allow users to unsubscribe by using the link at the bottom of each email.
16.0
NOTICES AND CONSENTS
Any notice, request, or other communication to either party by the other under this Policy shall be given by email, chat message, or conventional mail and shall be confirmed by visiting the link.
17.0
CHOICE/OPT-OUT
As discussed above, you can always choose not to provide information, although it may be required to engage in a certain activity on the website. We will send you information regarding updates about our products and promotional offers. You cannot opt-out of administrative emails.
"Administrative Emails" relate to a User's activity on the platform, and include emails regarding a particular user's account and requests or inquiries. If you do not wish to receive them, you have the option to deactivate your account. In contrast to administrative emails, however, you do have a choice with respect to promotional emails. Promotional emails advertise our products and services, and/or the products and services of our advertisers and affiliates. If you do not want to receive promotional emails from us, you may select to opt-out of receiving promotional emails at any time after registering by hitting the "unsubscribe" button at the bottom of any of our e-mails. When contacting us, please indicate your name, address, email address, and which promotional emails you do not want to receive.
